headline: 3 Consumer Stocks with Open Questions
summary: Retailers are overhauling their operations as technology redefines the shopping experience. Still, demand can be volatile as the industry is exposed to the ups and downs of consumer spending. This has stirred some uncertainty lately as retail stocks have lagged the market over the past six months, posting a return of 20.3% compared to 22.9% for the S&P 500.
